Kubernetes
Commands:
minkube start; (minikube is only used to start or stop the service)
but in commands we only use kubectl
kubectl get nodes;
kubectl get status;
kubectl get pods;(pods is the smallest unit of Kubernetes architecture)
kubectl create deployment nginxdepl --image=nginx; (to create a pod of nginx)
kubectl get deployment;
kubectl get replicaset; (replicaset is managing the replicas of pods)
kubectl edit deployment nginx-depl (edit the config file of image ex: changing version of nginx etc)
kubectl exec -it nginx-depl-54bd6589c-99hbb -- bin/bash (to enter the terminal of image ex nginx or ubuntu for debugging purposes)
